args:
A squad under Joachim's command has been
tasked with rescuing a team of negotiators.
With Noelle's assistance, they manage to
cross the border and infiltrate Barthe.
At a forest near the Barthe border...
So, um, over there. The negotiators are\nbeing held in that camp.
Damn. It's guarded tighter than a\nhenhouse in fox country.
(What SHOULD we do?\nSplit into two, maybe?)
(One group can act as a decoy to draw\ntheir forces, while the other sneaks in\nand rescues the captives.)
(If they see through the plan, it'll mean\nI sent everyone to their deaths.)
(It'd be my sister all over again...)
Stop starin' into space and DO\nsomething already!
Sir, are you feeling all right?\nYou look a bit pale.
Aw, to hell with it. Looks like the only\noption is to charge in directly!
My life is in your hands!
(Well, hell. If I don't give an order soon,\nthey're all gonna end up dead anyway.)
Prepare for battle! We move as one!
Just wait a second. I have a plan.
(I can't sit by and watch them die.\nI won't lose anyone else—never again!)
Captain! Our scouts report that a large\nSvenitlan force is approaching!
Come for the hostages, no doubt.\nPrepare a counterattack.
Please forgive my breach of protocol, sir,\nbut shouldn't we consider the possibility\nthat this could be a diversion?

Our borders are sealed tight, sir.
It stretches the boundaries of logic
to think a large force could have
snuck up on us unseen.
A valid point. Which would mean...
They plan to draw our attention with\nthis charade, then steal the hostages\nout from under our noses!
We need more intelligence before making\na decision one way or the other.
Shall we move the hostages to the\ninnermost part of the camp to be safe?
Do it. These fools will soon learn Barthe\nis not so easily deceived as all that!
What is it, soldier?\nDid you find the Svenitlan army?
Just a few stragglers in the woods, sir.
Then it IS a diversion! They'll surely\nattempt to infiltrate our camp soon,\nso increase security around the hostages.
Uh, regarding that, sir. The hostages\nseem to have...um...escaped.
Ha ha ha! I can't believe we pulled it off!
Joachim's strategy worked like a charm!
I never would've come up with that.\nYou really pulled the wool over their eyes!
It's all of you who deserve the credit.\nThanks for trusting my orders.
(Phew! The plan worked. Maybe now\nI can get back in Kirsty's good graces.)
Right then. Let's use the tunnel and... Huh?
Why is Noelle running toward us?
The Barthe army has mounted a full\noffensive on the mountain base!
Damn. They were short-handed enough\nBEFORE our squad departed.
(It'll take too much time for us to crawl\nback through that tiny tunnel...)
We need a plan here! How are we\ngoing to rescue the commander?
We'll do whatever it takes, sir!\nPlease give your orders!
Right! Forget the tunnel—we're going to\ncross the border and engage the enemy\nin a direct frontal assault!
That's what I like to hear!\nTo arms, men! To arms!
